sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains a red fluorescence protein followed by double terminator, the RFP has no preceding rbs sequence
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: YU Bin, Qiang Qin Qin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Both the RFP and the terminator are from the registry

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of a fusion protein Lpp-rbs-protein under the pLac promoter. The Lpp is a signal peptide. The ompA domain of the fusion directs the protein to the surface membrane. The pLac promoter can be repressed by LacI protein. This part lacks a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yu bin, Jiang QinQin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pLac promoter, rbs sequence are obtained from the registry The fusion protein coding sequence is self-designed

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The streptavidin encoding gene fused with eGFP gene sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Liu chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Use this fusion protein to detect the gene expression and localization of streptavidin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J36837
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part codes for amino acids #46-159 of outer membrane protein A (OmpA). It corresponds to five transmembrane domains of OmpA, crossing the outer membrane of E. coli.
This was fused with the lipoprotein signal peptide upstream and streptavidin downstream in the project to express streptavidin on the outer surface of E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Perry Tsai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There are no spacer nucleotides between the part and the XbaI restriction site, or between the part and the SpeI restriction site, so that the mixed site would be 6bp long, and reading frame would be maintained between protein domains.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J36835
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This codes for the 20-amino-acid signal peptide and the 1st nine amino acids of lipoprotein. When fused with another protein downstream, the signal peptide should target the protein to the outer membrane of E. coli, facing the periplasm.
This part was fused with OmpA(aa46-66) and OmpA(aa46-159) in trying to express streptavidin protein on the outer surface of E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Perry Tsai
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is no spacer nucleotide between the part and the SpeI restriction site, so that after BioBricks assembly, the mixed site is 6 base pairs, and the reading frame is maintained between protein domains.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
